snippet: Hannah Warren, who would have been 3 in August, died from complications after a separate surgery on her esophagus. She was the youngest person ever to receive a bioengineered organ.
abstract: Hannah Warren, toddler who in April 2013 became youngest person ever to receive a bioengineered organ, dies at Children's Hospital of Illinois from complications after separate surgery on her esophagus; Warren, who was born without a trachea and received a bioengineered windpipe implant, would have turned 3 years old in August.
lead_paragraph: Hannah Warren, who would have been 3 in August, died from complications after a separate surgery on her esophagus. She was the youngest person ever to receive a bioengineered organ.

headline.main: Young Girl Given Bioengineered Windpipe Dies
